The paper discusses recommender systems, which are typically studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of random walks is a graph-based approach, which is also studied in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the classification of different approaches, which is a task that falls under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, since the paper is a survey, it could also be classified under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC) sub-category, which includes studies on social media and online communities.
